<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="61" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1685,1905]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,285,1685,1711]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[428,500,1686,1711]" class="Arachnida" family="Barychelidae" genus="Sason" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[428,500,1686,1711]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">Sason</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the genera 
<taxonomicName box="[797,1027,1686,1711]" class="Arachnida" family="Barychelidae" genus="Paracenobiopelma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[797,1027,1686,1711]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">Paracenobiopelma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1087,1244,1686,1711]" class="Arachnida" family="Barychelidae" genus="Cosmopelma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1087,1244,1686,1711]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">Cosmopelma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in not having a clypeus; from 
<emphasis box="[325,645,1725,1750]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicName box="[325,476,1725,1750]" class="Arachnida" family="Barychelidae" genus="Sipalolasma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Sipalolasma</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[489,645,1725,1750]" class="Arachnida" family="Barychelidae" genus="Cosmopelma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Cosmopelma</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[705,839,1725,1750]" class="Arachnida" family="Barychelidae" genus="Sasonichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[705,839,1725,1750]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">Sasonichus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the ocular group rectangular, and from 
<taxonomicName box="[151,304,1763,1788]" class="Arachnida" family="Barychelidae" genus="Cosmopelma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,304,1763,1788]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">Cosmopelma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[361,493,1763,1788]" class="Arachnida" family="Barychelidae" genus="Sasonichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[361,493,1763,1788]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">Sasonichus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having strong and linear cuspules on labium of females (
<bibRefCitation author="Raven" box="[1193,1338,1763,1789]" pageId="1" pageNumber="67" refString="Raven, R. J. (1985) The spider infraorder Mygalomorphae (Araneae): cladistics and systematics. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 182 (1), 1 - 180." type="journal article" year="1985">Raven 1985</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Raven" box="[1350,1413,1763,1789]" pageId="1" pageNumber="67" refString="Raven, R. J. (1986) A revision of the spider genus Sason Simon (Sasoninae, Barychelidae Mygalomorphae) and its historical biogeography. Journal of Arachnology, 14, 47 - 70." type="journal article" year="1986">1986</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
